
    Role and Titles: Data analysts may not always have "data analyst" in their job title but often have "analyst" in some form. They might be called operations analysts or marketing analysts, depending on the organization.
    Skills and Knowledge: Data analysts have a deeper understanding of data systems, database designs, and SQL querying. They also understand data governance and are skilled in cleaning and transforming data.
    Growth Areas: To advance, data analysts should deepen their knowledge in statistics, functions (like IF and aggregate functions), joins, and soft skills such as active listening, data storytelling, and critical thinking.

